{"lemma":"عاقِبَة","slug":"عاقِبَة","root":"ع.ق.ب","root_slug":"ع-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عاقِبَة","root":"عقب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":32},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29827","n29853"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"consequence, ramification, aftermath (result of actions, especially if such a result is unwanted or unpleasant)","examples":[{"text":"وَإِلَّا سَتَكُون العَوَاقِب وَخِيمَة","english":"otherwise consequences will be severe"},{"text":"وَلَقَدْ بَعَثْنَا فِي كُلِّ أُمَّةٍ رَسُولًا أَنِ ٱعْبُدُوا اللّٰهَ وَٱجْتَنِبُوا ٱلطَّاغُوتَ ۖ فَمِنْهُم مَّنْ هَدَى اللّٰهُ وَمِنْهُم مَنْ حَقَّتْ عَلَيْهِ ٱلضَّلَالَةُ ۚ فَسِيرُوا فِي ٱلْأَرْضِ فَٱنْظُرُوا كَيْفَ كَانَ عَاقِبَةُ ٱلْمُكَذِّبِينَ","english":"And we certainly sent into every nation a messenger [saying] “worship God and avoid the idol”. And among them were those whom God guided, and among them were those upon whom error was deservedly enacted. So proceed through the earth and see how was the end of the deniers."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"offspring","tags":["historical"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the feminine form of active participle of the verb عَقَبَ (ʕaqaba)."},"ipa":["/ʕaː.qi.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29827","headword_ar":"عاقبهُ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, second sentence. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAqb","text_ar":"عاقب"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajula","text_ar":"الرَّجُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, * TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaAqabapN","text_ar":"مُعَاقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqaAbN","text_ar":"عِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did a thing with the man alternately, each taking his turn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEqbhu","text_ar":"اعقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And [particularly], (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaAqabapN","text_ar":"مُعَاقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rode in his turn after the man, each riding in his turn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEqbhu","text_ar":"اعقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtqbhu","text_ar":"اعتقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqabotu","text_ar":"عَاقَبْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajula fiY Alr~aAHilapi","text_ar":"الرَّجُلَ فِى الرَّاحِلَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I rode in my turn after the man, upon the camel, he riding in his turn after me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) And in like manner you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotaqabuwhu","text_ar":"اِعْتَقَبُوهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaAqabuwhu","text_ar":"تَعَاقَبُوهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They rode by turns with him, taking their turns after him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAqb bayona Al$~ayoy^ayoni","text_ar":"عاقب بَيْنَ الشَّيْيَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made an interchange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alternation between the two things; he made the two things interchangeable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commutable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he brought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did, the two things interchangeably,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alternately,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of them one time and the other of them another time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Thus, for instance,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEarabu tuEaAqibu bayona AlfaA='i wAlv~aA='i","text_ar":"العَرَبُ تُعَاقِبُ بَيْنَ الفَا=ءِ والثَّا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Arabs make an interchange between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interchangeable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commutable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadafN","text_ar":"جَدَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadavN","text_ar":"جَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuEoqibu","text_ar":"تُعْقِبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (S, O.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAqb","text_ar":"عاقب"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stood upon one of his legs one time and upon the other another time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moved his legs alternately."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAqbhu","text_ar":"عاقبهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as denoting consequence, and retaliation, or retribution, also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He punished him."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAqbhu bi*anobihi","text_ar":"عاقبهُ بِذَنْبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, * TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqaAbN","text_ar":"عِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaAqabapN","text_ar":"مُعَاقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He punished him for his crime, sin, fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, * TA:) and [in like manner] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEq~bhu","text_ar":"تعقّبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He punished him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. a man, S, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for a crime, a sin, a fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an offence, that he had committed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) In the saying in the Kur [xvi. last verse but one],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_ino EaAqabotumo faEaAqibuwA bimivoli maA EuwqibotumN bihi","text_ar":"وَاـِنْ عَاقَبْتُمْ فَعَاقِبُوا بِمِثْلِ مَا عُوقِبْتُمٌ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And if ye punish, then punish ye with the like of that with which ye have been afflicted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"punished"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the verb first denotes punishment, and is afterwards used for the purpose of assimilation: and similar to this is the saying in the same [xxii. 59],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamano EaAqaba bimivoli maA Euwqiba bihi","text_ar":"وَمَنْ عَاقَبَ بِمِثْلِ مَا عُوقِبَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And whoso punisheth with the like of that with which he hath been afflicted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"punished"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) For another ex., from the Kur lx. 11, [where it implies retaliation or retribution,] see 1, latter half. [In like manner,] it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboTala Aln~afoHa A_il~aA A^ano yuDoraba","text_ar":"اَبْطَلَ النَّفْحَ اـِلَّا اَنْ يُضْرَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayuEaAqiba","text_ar":"فَيُعَاقِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the kicking"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a beast"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the hind leg to be of no account unless it were beaten"},{"kind":"text","text":"by its master, or rider,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and retaliated"},{"kind":"text","text":"by kicking another person]; meaning, he made nothing to be incumbent on the master of the beast unless the latter made the kicking to be a consequence of that [i. e. unless the beast kicked in consequence of its being beaten by the master, or rider]. (TA.) [See also 4, which has a similar meaning, that of requital.] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euwqibato","text_ar":"عُوقِبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a mare means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She was required to perform run after run."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 277.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","TA","S","O","K","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n29853","headword_ar":"عَاقِبَةٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a quasi-inf. n.: see 1, first quarter. ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}